				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: The Secrets of Power Leveling from 20-50<a name="22060"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Feb 18 04 2:12 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>The lv 65 bard runs into the local dungeon/hunting area, and pulls 30-40 mobs (may need to have your lv 65 friend get buffs first depending on his/her gear). 
<br />
They twist in all there DS should be able to bust out around 100 DS (Damage shield) on them selves, You play 1 AE blast chant. rinse repeat. You should hit 50 in from 1-50 in a 1-2 days played tops.
<br />

<br />
Keep in mind though you:
<br />
A. will lack any skill in playing the class
<br />
B. will have no trained skills
<br />
C. no grouping/twist skills for your bard 
<br />

<br />
once your 50 I would recomend if not sooner to make sure you try soloing some and grouping some so you get a feel for your class and learn how to twist your songs. This also helps work your defense/melee skills at the same time.
<br />

<br />
Now for your songs just when you log out for the night leave your self in a safe spot playing your tunes.
<br />

<br />
Hope this helps and best luck<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" /></span></td>
			</tr><tr>
