				<td colspan="2"><span>are you dual boxing aka Hydra?  If so, you really have to be on your game, juggling both at the same time.  I do it and it's hard.  I did it with my friends Druid, and I would stay grouped for group buffs and to monitor my bards health from one computer.  Right before the mob dies I would break the group up by disbanding with the druid, leaving bard to hack the last few % of health, regroup and repeat.  Figure you could do that with another bard...have him play haste and heal twist while your bard assists on the mob, then break group from higher bard leaving your lower bard to go at the mob and xp should always go to you...higher lvl bard needs to lose agro tho at the end by fading or invis...or just backing up leaving you there laying the smack down...hehe...
