				<td colspan="2"><span>The idea is for the level 65 to get and keep agro.  The lower level bard sits back and does nothing until it is almost all over.  The mobs beat themselves to death on the lvl 65 and his DS.  The lower level bard cleans up and gets exp.  In the case described with the druid above, the druid was getting the advantage of the bards DS in addition to his own.  Breaking the group was necessary to avoid splitting or defaulting the exp.  This makes things faster but isnt necessary until later levels.</span></td>
