				<td colspan="2"><span>exactly Tin...as usual you clean up my mess.  hahaha.  Sorry for the msg being oddly worded, but what Tinuvien said was what I meant.  It helps to get the ds and healing from a high level druid, but in between til the beginning of the next fight regroup to maintain group buffs with druid.  Then disband group as you hack the mob down, root from druid, but be careful not to do too much dmg with druid or you will lose aggro and yes, lose xp of the mob.  I usually just stick to root the mob, ds my bard, let my bard chant it from a distance.  keep a low level root on it so dmg is less so my dmg keeps aggro and voila.  xp and hardly a scratch.
